            <h2><u>Vidar</u>bha</h2>
        </section>
        <p>Vidarbha is a culturally rich region located in the eastern part of Maharashtra, known for its diverse
            traditions, historical significance, and lush landscapes. Major cities like Nagpur, Amravati, and Yavatmal
            are part of this region, each contributing to its unique cultural tapestry. Vidarbha is famous for its
            agriculture, particularly oranges, and is often referred to as the "Orange City." The region is also home to
            various historical sites, temples, and forts that showcase its heritage. Festivals like Diwali and Makar
            Sankranti are celebrated with great fervor, reflecting the community spirit and traditions of Vidarbha.</p>

