        <section>
            <h2><u>Festi</u>vals</h2>
            <p>Vidarbha is known for its vibrant festivals:</p>
        </section>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Diwali:</strong> The festival of lights, symbolizing the victory of light over darkness.</li>
            <p>Diwali, celebrated across India, holds a special significance in Vidarbha. The festival marks the return
                of Lord Rama to Ayodhya and signifies the victory of good over evil. Homes are decorated with diyas
                (lamps), rangoli (colorful patterns), and lights, creating a vibrant atmosphere. Families come together
                to perform puja, exchange sweets, and burst fireworks, adding to the celebratory spirit. The warmth of
                community gatherings and festive activities makes Diwali a cherished occasion in Vidarbha.</p>
            <p>
                During Diwali, families come together to share delicious traditional sweets and snacks, such as karanjis
                and besan ladoos. The evenings are filled with the sound of firecrackers and the glow of diyas lighting
                up the night sky. Community events, cultural programs, and exchanges of gifts further enhance the spirit
                of togetherness. In Vidarbha, Diwali is not just a religious occasion but also a time to reinforce
                family bonds and celebrate the region’s rich cultural heritage.
            </p>

