            <li><strong>Bail Pola:</strong> A harvest festival celebrated with kite flying and traditional sweets.
            </li>
            <p>Bail Pola is a traditional festival celebrated in Vidarbha, primarily dedicated to honoring the bullocks,
                which are vital for agriculture in the region. Observed during the month of Shravan (July-August), this
                festival showcases the deep-rooted agricultural traditions of the local communities.</p>
            <p>
                On Bail Pola, farmers decorate their bullocks with colorful garlands, bells, and sometimes even
                intricate patterns painted on their bodies. The celebration includes rituals of worship, where farmers
                offer prayers for the well-being and strength of their animals. This day also features various cultural
                activities, including folk songs and dances, as families come together to express gratitude for the
                bullocks’ hard work throughout the year. The festival not only highlights the significance of these
                animals in farming but also fosters community bonding and cultural identity in Vidarbha.
            </p>

