            <li><strong>Gudi Padwa:</strong> Celebrated as the Marathi New Year, symbolizing new beginnings.</li>
            <p>Gudi Padwa marks the start of the Marathi New Year and is celebrated with enthusiasm in Vidarbha. The
                festival features the hoisting of the "Gudi," a decorated pole adorned with a bright cloth and flowers,
                symbolizing prosperity. Traditional dishes like puran poli are prepared, and the atmosphere is filled
                with joyous celebrations, family gatherings, and community spirit.</p>

