                curries.</li>
            <p>Bajra Khichdi is a wholesome and nutritious dish popular in Vidarbha, made primarily from pearl millet
                (bajra) and lentils. This dish is often cooked with various spices, vegetables, and a hint of ghee,
                making it both flavorful and comforting.</p>
            <p>Rich in dietary fiber and essential nutrients, Bajra Khichdi is not only a staple in rural households but
                also a preferred choice during winter months due to its warming properties. Typically served with
                yogurt, pickles, or green chutney, it provides a balanced meal that's easy to digest and ideal for
                maintaining energy levels throughout the day. The simplicity and heartiness of Bajra Khichdi make it a
                beloved comfort food in the region.</p>

