        <ul>
            <li><strong>Kalamkari:</strong> Renowned handwoven sarees known for their elegance and intricate
                designs.</li>
            <p>
                Kalamkari is a traditional Indian art form known for its intricate hand-painted or block-printed designs on fabric. Originating in regions like Andhra Pradesh and Telangana, it has gained popularity in Vidarbha as well. The term "kalamkari" is derived from "kalam," meaning pen, and "kari," meaning work, reflecting the pen-like tool used for painting</p>

